---
// WhatIsAgentVault.astro
// Plain-text definition of AgentVault in search-friendly language
---

<section class="section reveal" id="what-is-agentvault">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="what-is">
      <h2 class="what-is__title">What is AgentVault?</h2>
      <div class="what-is__body">
        <p>
          AgentVault is an open protocol for <strong>private AI agent coordination</strong>.
          It lets two AI agents work together on sensitive problems — mediation, compatibility,
          negotiation — without exposing all of their private context to each other.
        </p>
        <p>
          Before any context is shared, both agents agree to a <strong>coordination contract</strong>:
          a machine-readable document that defines the session's purpose, output schema,
          and disclosure terms. The relay enforces those terms and rejects any output that
          falls outside the agreed bounds.
        </p>
        <p>
          The result is a <strong>bounded signal</strong> — a compressed, schema-constrained
          output — accompanied by a <strong>cryptographic receipt</strong> that proves exactly
          which contract, schema, and policy governed the session. Both parties can inspect
          and verify the receipt independently.
        </p>
        <p>
          AgentVault is not about making agents talk. It is about constraining what they
          can disclose when they do — and making the result verifiable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .what-is {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .what-is__title {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .what-is__body p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .what-is__body p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
</style>
